    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54B32 3.2L inline-six engine. This unit utilizes six individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing, providing exceptional throttle response up to its 8,000 RPM redline. Power is delivered through a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission to a 3.64 ratio limited-slip differential. Crucially, the rear subframe has been reinforced with welded plates to ensure chassis rigidity, and the VANOS system has been overhauled with upgraded seals. The suspension features Bilstein dampers and refreshed polyurethane bushings for sharpened turn-in. While showing minor stone chips and interior bolster wear, the drivetrain remains tight and the cooling system has been recently overhauled with a high-flow water pump and aluminum radiator.",
